DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,5);
$b = random(1,5);
$c = random(1,2);
$ab = $a + $b ;

$ans1 =  sqrt(6);
$ans2 = 2*($a**2)*(sqrt(6))*(4/5);

$NO_SPACE = '@{\,}';

BEGIN_TEXT

The following parametric equations trace out a loop.
\[ \begin{array}{r${NO_SPACE}c${NO_SPACE}l}
x & = & $ab-\frac{$a}{2} t^2          \cr
y & = & -\frac{$a}{6}t^3+ $a t  + $c  
\end{array} \]
Find the \(t\) values at which the curve intersects itself:  
$BR
\( t = \pm \)  \{ ans_rule(10) \}.
END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));

BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
What is the total area inside the loop?
$BR
Area =  \{ ans_rule(50) \}.
END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp($ans2));

ENDDOCUMENT();



